key_facts: AI Engineers are responsible for transforming AI models from ideas to practical systems.
Deep learning is not the only choice; traditional machine learning algorithms can also be effective.
Understanding business problems and data quality is crucial before building an AI model.
AI Engineers need to work with various roles including Data Engineers, Backend Engineers, DevOps or Cloud Engineers.
Data issues like bias, privacy concerns, and ethical implications are important in AI development.
Debugging and improving models after deployment require continuous monitoring.
Mathematical foundations such as probability, linear algebra, and optimization are essential for AI Engineers.
open_questions: What is the typical starting point of an AI project?
How do AI Engineers handle wrong model results?
